[summary:string]
A talk for the React Buenos Aires meetup (a special June edition co-hosted with Howdy) about technical planning *before* writing code. In React projects, many tasks start with too many implicit decisions—structure, state, component boundaries, effects, data, edge cases. I share an upfront planning approach that makes those decisions visible before implementing, and that lets you feed AI better context from the start: less friction, lower cognitive load, and better technical conversations in the team.

