[content:md]
This is a special June edition of the **React Buenos Aires** meetup, co-hosted with the Howdy team, dedicated to software development and community. Doors open at 6:30 PM and talks start at 7:00 PM sharp.

![Meetup Junio — React Buenos Aires + Howdy](/assets/react-buenos-aires-2026-cover.jpg#center)

### Planificar antes de codear (+ aún en tiempos de AI)
In React projects, many tasks kick off with too many *implicit* decisions: structure, state, the boundaries between components, effects, data, edge cases. In this talk I share an approach to **upfront technical planning** that makes those decisions visible before implementing—and that lets you use AI with better context from the very beginning.

The payoff is concrete: less friction, lower cognitive load, and higher-quality technical conversations within the team. Far from being made obsolete by AI, deliberate planning is what gives an AI assistant the context it needs to actually help.

This is one of two talks of the evening, alongside Raúl Ahumada's "¿Y si tu backend fuera tan reactivo como tu frontend?" about reactive backends for React apps with Convex.

